criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Diagnosis of knee osteoarthritis according to the clinical and radiographic criteria
             of the American College of Rheumatology: signs of osteoarthritis in at least one of
             the compartments of the knee joint (tibiofemoral and / or in the patellofemoral
             joint); grade 2 or 3, according to Kellgren & Lawrence criteria in the radiographic
             examination;

          -  Minimum score of 04 cm on the Visual Analogue Scale (EVA, total of 10 cm);

          -  Accept and sign the informed consent form.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Regular practice of moderate or intense physical activity for more than 45 minutes a
             week;

          -  Having started physical activity or undergone any physical therapy treatment in the
             previous 3 months;

          -  Use of corticosteroid infiltration in the knee (previous 6 months);

          -  Performing previous surgery on the knee or hip;

          -  Presence of some clinical restriction that makes it impossible for them to participate
             in the proposed evaluations or interventions (cardiorespiratory, neurological,
             musculoskeletal, vascular changes, and / or the presence of skin lesions when applying
             the bandage).
